# Goal definition
# Kick direction as an (x, y) vector in the robot's body frame (+x forward,
# +y left); the policy uses atan2(y, x) as the kick heading. strength is the
# kick-speed target passed to the policy. The kick stays active for `timeout`
# seconds, after which the node clears the kick. timeout < 0 means "use the
# node's configured default".
float64 x
float64 y
float64 strength # should be 1-5 to be in distribution for the current policy
float64 timeout -1.0
---
# Result definition
uint8 SUCCESS=0
uint8 UNREACHABLE=1
uint8 ABORTED=2
uint8 REJECTED=3

uint8 result
---
# Feedback definition
float64 time_remaining
